{
  "texts": [
    "Preclinical AD is the first stage, where blood, brain, and CSF abnormalities occur without symptoms.",
    "Thus, contemporary life's beginning is no longer clear.",
    "The typical test struggles to detect AD early on, when the changes are too minor.",
    "Early AD detection is hindered by stigma, a lack of dementia care training, and the importance of early diagnosis (Dubois et al., 2009).",
    "Confusing dementia-like disorders with cognitive impairment (delirium, melancholy, vitamin deficiencies)."
  ]
}